      <a href="index.html?p=702#comment-21098"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2012-09-19T21:55:31-04:00">Wednesday, September 19, 2012 at 9:55 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I just returned from Barcelona and this is the way the restaurants make and serve gazpacho &#8212; it is delicious.  It is also similar to the gazpacho recipe in the Food of Spain by Claudia Roden.  But he leaves out the cucumbers and uses them as a garnish and also adds a big slice of toasted white bread in the blender &#8212; it adds to the creaminess.</p>
    </div>

